// drop_observable.fuse — W09-P05-T01 Drop proof.
//
// At W09 the checker accepts a `struct` with an `impl Drop` block
// and the liveness pass records a DropIntent for every local of
// that type, then MIR codegen emits `TypeName_drop(&_lN);` for
// each intent. The full pipeline-to-binary path for observing
// Drop requires the spine to support multi-statement bodies and
// the stdlib to expose a counter — neither is in scope until
// W15+ and W22+.
//
// W09's proof therefore ships as a source fixture (this file)
// plus a Go test (`TestDropObservable`) that drives the liveness
// pass directly against a synthetic Drop-scenario program and
// confirms the DropIntent list is non-empty. The .fuse source
// below exercises the checker/monomorph path for the Drop trait
// declaration and the `impl Drop for D` block; the full
// observable-exit path lands when the spine expands.

trait Drop {
    fn drop(self);
}

struct D {
    value: I32,
}

impl D : Drop {
    fn drop(self) {
        return;
    }
}

fn main() -> I32 {
    return 0;
}
